{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":904,"text":"I want you to, for a moment,"},{"time":3452,"text":"think about playing a game of Monopoly."},{"time":7087,"text":"Except in this game,\nthat combination of skill, talent and luck"},{"time":12532,"text":"that helped earn you success\nin games, as in life,"},{"time":15311,"text":"has been rendered irrelevant,"},{"time":16736,"text":"because this game's been rigged,"},{"time":18916,"text":"and you've got the upper hand."},{"time":20795,"text":"You've got more money,"},{"time":22603,"text":"more opportunities to move\naround the board,"},{"time":25164,"text":"and more access to resources."},{"time":27398,"text":"And as you think about that experience,"},{"time":29292,"text":"I want you to ask yourself:"},{"time":31105,"text":"How might that experience of being\na privileged player in a rigged game"},{"time":36176,"text":"change the way you think about yourself"},{"time":39168,"text":"and regard that other player?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":42914,"text":"So, we ran a study\non the UC Berkeley campus"},{"time":46019,"text":"to look at exactly that question."},{"time":48283,"text":"We brought in more than 100 pairs\nof strangers into the lab,"},{"time":52857,"text":"and with the flip of a coin,"},{"time":54595,"text":"randomly assigned one of the two\nto be a rich player in a rigged game."},{"time":58660,"text":"They got two times as much money;"},{"time":61509,"text":"when they passed Go,\nthey collected twice the salary;"},{"time":65339,"text":"and they got to roll\nboth dice instead of one,"},{"time":67644,"text":"so they got to move\naround the board a lot more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69962,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72018,"text":"And over the course of 15 minutes,"},{"time":73750,"text":"we watched through\nhidden cameras what happened."},{"time":77257,"text":"What I want to do today,\nfor the first time,"},{"time":79377,"text":"is show you a little bit of what we saw."},{"time":81549,"text":"You'll to have to pardon\nthe sound quality,"},{"time":83874,"text":"because again, these were hidden cameras."},{"time":85871,"text":"So we've provided subtitles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87951,"text":"[Video] Rich Player: How many\n500s did you have?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90290,"text":"Poor Player: Just one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91465,"text":"RP: Are you serious?\nPP: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92909,"text":"RP: I have three. (Laughs)\nI don't know why they gave me so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96064,"text":"Paul Piff: So it was quickly apparent\nto players that something was up."},{"time":99453,"text":"One person clearly has\na lot more money than the other person,"},{"time":102604,"text":"and yet, as the game unfolded,"},{"time":105184,"text":"we saw very notable differences,\ndramatic differences begin to emerge"},{"time":109738,"text":"between the two players."},{"time":111488,"text":"The rich player started to move\naround the board louder,"},{"time":115831,"text":"literally smacking the board\nwith the piece as he went around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118879,"text":"(Game piece smacks board)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120610,"text":"We were more likely\nto see signs of dominance"},{"time":123583,"text":"and nonverbal signs, displays of power"},{"time":127620,"text":"and celebration among the rich players."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131500,"text":"We had a bowl of pretzels\npositioned off to the side."},{"time":134209,"text":"It's on the bottom right corner."},{"time":135775,"text":"That allowed us to watch\nparticipants' consummatory behavior."},{"time":139258,"text":"So we're just tracking\nhow many pretzels participants eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143782,"text":"[Video] RP: Are those pretzels a trick?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145753,"text":"PP: I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147713,"text":"Paul Piff: OK, so no surprises,\npeople are on to us."},{"time":150852,"text":"They wonder what that bowl of pretzels\nis doing there in the first place."},{"time":154368,"text":"One even asks, like you just saw,"},{"time":156026,"text":"\"Is that bowl of pretzels\nthere as a trick?\""},{"time":159035,"text":"And yet, despite that,\nthe power of the situation"},{"time":162103,"text":"seems to inevitably dominate,"},{"time":164337,"text":"and those rich players\nstart to eat more pretzels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167396,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172290,"text":"[Video] RP: I love pretzels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173726,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178314,"text":"Paul Piff: And as the game went on,"},{"time":180448,"text":"one of the really interesting\nand dramatic patterns"},{"time":182947,"text":"that we observed begin to emerge"},{"time":186254,"text":"was that the rich players\nactually started to become ruder"},{"time":189080,"text":"toward the other person --"},{"time":191103,"text":"less and less sensitive to the plight\nof those poor, poor players,"},{"time":194729,"text":"and more and more demonstrative\nof their material success,"},{"time":199288,"text":"more likely to showcase\nhow well they're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204084,"text":"[Video] RP: I have money ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205741,"text":"(Laughs) I have money for everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208013,"text":"PP: How much is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209510,"text":"RP: You owe me 24 dollars."},{"time":213404,"text":"You're going to lose all your money soon."},{"time":216135,"text":"I'll buy it. I have so much money."},{"time":218295,"text":"I have so much money, it takes me forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220345,"text":"RP 2: I'm going\nto buy out this whole board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222458,"text":"RP 3: You're going\nto run out of money soon."},{"time":224563,"text":"I'm pretty much untouchable at this point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228247,"text":"Paul Piff: And here's what I think\nwas really, really interesting:"},{"time":231456,"text":"it's that, at the end of the 15 minutes,"},{"time":234298,"text":"we asked the players to talk\nabout their experience during the game."},{"time":238647,"text":"And when the rich players talked\nabout why they had inevitably won"},{"time":242757,"text":"in this rigged game of Monopoly ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244453,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249468,"text":"They talked about what they'd done\nto buy those different properties"},{"time":255840,"text":"and earn their success in the game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257829,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258887,"text":"And they became far less attuned"},{"time":261311,"text":"to all those different\nfeatures of the situation --"},{"time":263847,"text":"including that flip of a coin --"},{"time":266503,"text":"that had randomly gotten them\ninto that privileged position"},{"time":270526,"text":"in the first place."},{"time":271853,"text":"And that's a really,\nreally incredible insight"},{"time":274710,"text":"into how the mind\nmakes sense of advantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280101,"text":"Now, this game of Monopoly can be used"},{"time":282303,"text":"as a metaphor for understanding society\nand its hierarchical structure,"},{"time":287286,"text":"wherein some people\nhave a lot of wealth and a lot of status,"},{"time":290927,"text":"and a lot of people don't;"},{"time":292435,"text":"they have a lot less wealth\nand a lot less status"},{"time":295348,"text":"and a lot less access to valued resources."},{"time":298420,"text":"And what my colleagues and I\nfor the last seven years have been doing"},{"time":301826,"text":"is studying the effects\nof these kinds of hierarchies."},{"time":305706,"text":"What we've been finding\nacross dozens of studies"},{"time":309109,"text":"and thousands of participants\nacross this country"},{"time":312485,"text":"is that as a person's levels\nof wealth increase,"},{"time":317088,"text":"their feelings of compassion\nand empathy go down,"},{"time":323038,"text":"and their feelings of entitlement,\nof deservingness,"},{"time":326788,"text":"and their ideology\nof self-interest increase."},{"time":331284,"text":"In surveys, we've found"},{"time":332901,"text":"that it's actually wealthier individuals\nwho are more likely to moralize"},{"time":336788,"text":"greed being good,"},{"time":338519,"text":"and that the pursuit of self-interest\nis favorable and moral."},{"time":343063,"text":"Now, what I want to do today\nis talk about some of the implications"},{"time":346717,"text":"of this ideology self-interest,"},{"time":349668,"text":"talk about why we should\ncare about those implications,"},{"time":352336,"text":"and end with what might be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355565,"text":"Some of the first studies\nthat we ran in this area"},{"time":358006,"text":"looked at helping behavior,"},{"time":359366,"text":"something social psychologists\ncall \"pro-social behavior.\""},{"time":363453,"text":"And we were really interested"},{"time":364926,"text":"in who's more likely\nto offer help to another person:"},{"time":368444,"text":"someone who's rich or someone who's poor."},{"time":371555,"text":"In one of the studies,"},{"time":372847,"text":"we bring rich and poor members\nof the community into the lab,"},{"time":378389,"text":"and give each of them\nthe equivalent of 10 dollars."},{"time":381785,"text":"We told the participants they could keep\nthese 10 dollars for themselves,"},{"time":386021,"text":"or they could share\na portion of it, if they wanted to,"},{"time":388933,"text":"with a stranger, who's totally anonymous."},{"time":391301,"text":"They'll never meet that stranger;\nthe stranger will never meet them."},{"time":394582,"text":"And we just monitor how much people give."},{"time":397554,"text":"Individuals who made 25,000,\nsometimes under 15,000 dollars a year,"},{"time":402227,"text":"gave 44 percent more\nof their money to the stranger"},{"time":405568,"text":"than did individuals making\n150,000, 200,000 dollars a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410983,"text":"We've had people play games"},{"time":413809,"text":"to see who's more or less likely to cheat"},{"time":416499,"text":"to increase their chances\nof winning a prize."},{"time":418877,"text":"In one of the games,\nwe actually rigged a computer"},{"time":421650,"text":"so that die rolls over a certain score\nwere impossible --"},{"time":425354,"text":"You couldn't get above 12\nin this game, and yet ..."},{"time":430564,"text":"the richer you were, the more likely\nyou were to cheat in this game"},{"time":433777,"text":"to earn credits toward a $50 cash prize --"},{"time":437146,"text":"sometimes by three to four times as much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441106,"text":"We ran another study"},{"time":442294,"text":"where we looked at whether people\nwould be inclined to take candy"},{"time":446474,"text":"from a jar of candy\nthat we explicitly identified"},{"time":449138,"text":"as being reserved for children --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451042,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454662,"text":"I'm not kidding -- I know it sounds\nlike I'm making a joke."},{"time":459221,"text":"We explicitly told participants:"},{"time":461475,"text":"\"This candy is for children participating\nin a developmental lab nearby."},{"time":465832,"text":"They're in studies. This is for them.\""},{"time":467985,"text":"And we just monitored\nhow much candy participants took."},{"time":471567,"text":"Participants who felt rich\ntook two times as much candy"},{"time":474506,"text":"as participants who felt poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477675,"text":"We've even studied cars."},{"time":480315,"text":"Not just any cars,"},{"time":482008,"text":"but whether drivers\nof different kinds of cars"},{"time":485296,"text":"are more or less inclined\nto break the law."},{"time":488338,"text":"In one of these studies,"},{"time":490558,"text":"we looked at whether drivers\nwould stop for a pedestrian"},{"time":495309,"text":"that we had posed waiting\nto cross at a crosswalk."},{"time":498193,"text":"Now in California, as you all know,"},{"time":500065,"text":"because I'm sure we all do this,"},{"time":502493,"text":"it's the law to stop for a pedestrian\nwho's waiting to cross."},{"time":506434,"text":"So here's an example of how we did it."},{"time":508300,"text":"That's our confederate off to the left,\nposing as a pedestrian."},{"time":511867,"text":"He approaches as the red truck\nsuccessfully stops."},{"time":516219,"text":"In typical California fashion,"},{"time":518022,"text":"it's overtaken by the bus\nwho almost runs our pedestrian over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521015,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":522392,"text":"Now here's an example\nof a more expensive car,"},{"time":524621,"text":"a Prius, driving through,\nand a BMW doing the same."},{"time":531590,"text":"So we did this for hundreds of vehicles"},{"time":534029,"text":"on several days,"},{"time":536512,"text":"just tracking who stops and who doesn't."},{"time":540587,"text":"What we found was as the expensiveness\nof a car increased ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544864,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":546960,"text":"the drivers' tendencies\nto break the law increased as well."},{"time":550215,"text":"None of the cars -- none of the cars --"},{"time":553040,"text":"in our least expensive car category"},{"time":556135,"text":"broke the law."},{"time":557793,"text":"Close to 50 percent of the cars\nin our most expensive vehicle category"},{"time":562660,"text":"broke the law."},{"time":565550,"text":"We've run other studies,"},{"time":566822,"text":"finding that wealthier individuals\nare more likely to lie in negotiations,"},{"time":570733,"text":"to endorse unethical behavior at work,"},{"time":572948,"text":"like stealing cash from the cash register,"},{"time":575662,"text":"taking bribes, lying to customers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580697,"text":"Now, I don't mean to suggest"},{"time":582314,"text":"that it's only wealthy people\nwho show these patterns of behavior."},{"time":585912,"text":"Not at all -- in fact,\nI think that we all,"},{"time":588742,"text":"in our day-to-day, minute-by-minute lives,"},{"time":591685,"text":"struggle with these competing motivations"},{"time":594558,"text":"of when or if to put our own interests\nabove the interests of other people."},{"time":600273,"text":"And that's understandable,"},{"time":602573,"text":"because the American dream is an idea"},{"time":605494,"text":"in which we all have an equal opportunity\nto succeed and prosper,"},{"time":610353,"text":"as long as we apply\nourselves and work hard."},{"time":612933,"text":"And a piece of that means that sometimes,"},{"time":615666,"text":"you need to put your own interests"},{"time":618619,"text":"above the interests and well-being\nof other people around you."},{"time":622152,"text":"But what we're finding\nis that the wealthier you are,"},{"time":625547,"text":"the more likely you are to pursue\na vision of personal success,"},{"time":629411,"text":"of achievement and accomplishment,"},{"time":631760,"text":"to the detriment of others around you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634927,"text":"Here I've plotted for you\nthe mean household income"},{"time":638224,"text":"received by each fifth\nand top five percent of the population"},{"time":641484,"text":"over the last 20 years."},{"time":643579,"text":"In 1993,"},{"time":644837,"text":"the differences between the different\nquintiles of the population,"},{"time":647987,"text":"in terms of income,"},{"time":649199,"text":"are fairly egregious."},{"time":651732,"text":"It's not difficult to discern\nthat there are differences."},{"time":654446,"text":"But over the last 20 years,\nthat significant difference"},{"time":657299,"text":"has become a Grand Canyon of sorts"},{"time":659615,"text":"between those at the top\nand everyone else."},{"time":662663,"text":"In fact, the top 20 percent\nof our population"},{"time":666321,"text":"own close to 90 percent\nof the total wealth in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669444,"text":"We're at unprecedented levels\nof economic inequality."},{"time":675858,"text":"What that means is that wealth is not only\nbecoming increasingly concentrated"},{"time":679723,"text":"in the hands of a select group\nof individuals,"},{"time":682681,"text":"but the American dream\nis becoming increasingly unattainable"},{"time":687033,"text":"for an increasing majority of us."},{"time":690227,"text":"And if it's the case,\nas we've been finding,"},{"time":693050,"text":"that the wealthier you are,"},{"time":694523,"text":"the more entitled you feel to that wealth,"},{"time":697066,"text":"and the more likely you are\nto prioritize your own interests"},{"time":700088,"text":"above the interests of other people,"},{"time":701868,"text":"and be willing to do things\nto serve that self-interest,"},{"time":705417,"text":"well, then, there's no reason to think\nthat those patterns will change."},{"time":709108,"text":"In fact, there's every reason\nto think that they'll only get worse,"},{"time":712664,"text":"and that's what it would look like\nif things just stayed the same,"},{"time":715874,"text":"at the same linear rate,\nover the next 20 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720162,"text":"Now inequality -- economic inequality --"},{"time":722926,"text":"is something we should\nall be concerned about,"},{"time":725149,"text":"and not just because of those\nat the bottom of the social hierarchy,"},{"time":728776,"text":"but because individuals and groups"},{"time":731144,"text":"with lots of economic\ninequality do worse ..."},{"time":736349,"text":"not just the people\nat the bottom, everyone."},{"time":739206,"text":"There's a lot of really\ncompelling research"},{"time":741297,"text":"coming out from top labs\nall over the world,"},{"time":743981,"text":"showcasing the range of things\nthat are undermined"},{"time":748655,"text":"as economic inequality gets worse."},{"time":751195,"text":"Social mobility,\nthings we really care about,"},{"time":754048,"text":"physical health, social trust,"},{"time":756530,"text":"all go down as inequality goes up."},{"time":759486,"text":"Similarly, negative things\nin social collectives and societies,"},{"time":764035,"text":"things like obesity, and violence,"},{"time":766139,"text":"imprisonment, and punishment,"},{"time":767761,"text":"are exacerbated as economic\ninequality increases."},{"time":771911,"text":"Again, these are outcomes\nnot just experienced by a few,"},{"time":775478,"text":"but that resound\nacross all strata of society."},{"time":778940,"text":"Even people at the top\nexperience these outcomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782219,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":785307,"text":"This cascade of self-perpetuating,"},{"time":788913,"text":"pernicious, negative effects"},{"time":791422,"text":"could seem like something\nthat's spun out of control,"},{"time":794842,"text":"and there's nothing we can do about it,"},{"time":796754,"text":"certainly nothing\nwe as individuals could do."},{"time":799558,"text":"But in fact, we've been finding\nin our own laboratory research"},{"time":806520,"text":"that small psychological interventions,"},{"time":811695,"text":"small changes to people's values,"},{"time":814831,"text":"small nudges in certain directions,"},{"time":818212,"text":"can restore levels\nof egalitarianism and empathy."},{"time":821759,"text":"For instance, reminding people\nof the benefits of cooperation"},{"time":826056,"text":"or the advantages of community,"},{"time":828961,"text":"cause wealthier individuals\nto be just as egalitarian"},{"time":832797,"text":"as poor people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835369,"text":"In one study, we had people watch\na brief video, just 46 seconds long,"},{"time":840918,"text":"about childhood poverty"},{"time":843144,"text":"that served as a reminder of the needs\nof others in the world around them."},{"time":848257,"text":"And after watching that,"},{"time":850176,"text":"we looked at how willing people\nwere to offer up their own time"},{"time":854242,"text":"to a stranger presented to them\nin the lab, who was in distress."},{"time":859026,"text":"After watching this video, an hour later,"},{"time":862270,"text":"rich people became\njust as generous of their own time"},{"time":865674,"text":"to help out this other person, a stranger,"},{"time":867844,"text":"as someone who's poor,"},{"time":869313,"text":"suggesting that these differences\nare not innate or categorical,"},{"time":873595,"text":"but are so malleable\nto slight changes in people's values,"},{"time":877375,"text":"and little nudges of compassion\nand bumps of empathy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881172,"text":"And beyond the walls of our lab,"},{"time":882773,"text":"we're even beginning to see\nsigns of change in society."},{"time":886893,"text":"Bill Gates, one of our nation's\nwealthiest individuals,"},{"time":890065,"text":"in his Harvard commencement speech,"},{"time":892017,"text":"talked about the problem\nof inequality facing society"},{"time":894902,"text":"as being the most daunting challenge,"},{"time":897589,"text":"and talked about what must\nbe done to combat it,"},{"time":900447,"text":"saying, \"Humanity's greatest advances\nare not in its discoveries --"},{"time":905489,"text":"but in how those discoveries are applied"},{"time":908545,"text":"to reduce inequity.\""},{"time":911356,"text":"And there's the Giving Pledge,"},{"time":913309,"text":"in which more than 100\nof our nation's wealthiest individuals"},{"time":918077,"text":"are pledging half\nof their fortunes to charity."},{"time":921886,"text":"And there's the emergence of dozens\nof grassroots movements,"},{"time":927136,"text":"like \"We are the 1 percent,\""},{"time":929508,"text":"\"Resource Generation,\""},{"time":931556,"text":"or \"Wealth for Common Good,\""},{"time":933469,"text":"in which the most privileged\nmembers of the population,"},{"time":937832,"text":"members of the one percent and elsewhere,"},{"time":940800,"text":"people who are wealthy,"},{"time":942662,"text":"are using their own economic resources,"},{"time":946139,"text":"adults and youth alike --\nthat's what's most striking to me --"},{"time":950396,"text":"leveraging their own privilege,\ntheir own economic resources,"},{"time":953981,"text":"to combat inequality"},{"time":956846,"text":"by advocating for social policies,"},{"time":959866,"text":"changes in social values"},{"time":961748,"text":"and changes in people's behavior"},{"time":964143,"text":"that work against\ntheir own economic interests,"},{"time":967207,"text":"but that may ultimately\nrestore the American dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971420,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972664,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}